Lindani Myeni was shot by the police in Hawaii in he US (Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala has joined calls for a thorough investigation into the death of Lindani Myeni. The former South African rugby player was shot and killed by police in Hawaii last week. READ: Lindani Myeni's family to open wrongful death suit Officers claim he became violent when they arrived at a property where they had received a complaint about a burglary. But a lawyer for his family says he responded in a way that any other person would have, when confronted by police officers who did not identify themselves. Myeni's  body will be brought to South Africa on Friday.